Constructor :
    - it is block(similar to method) having same name as that of class_name
    - it doesn't have any return type , not even void .
    - the only modifiers applicable for constructor are public , protected , default and private
    - it executes automatically when we create object
    - used to initialize an object
    -3 types of constructor
            1.Default Constructor : - (no-arg constructor)
                                    - compiler creates constructor
            2.No-arg constructor  : - (user defined)
                                    -
            3.Parameterised constructor : - constructor with parameters

    - 2 ways to call constructor :
            1. Test t = new Test();
            2. new Test(); //no need to create reference i.e. t
    - Syntax :
    class Test
    {
        public Test()
        {

        }
        public static void main(String[] args)
        {
        Test t = new Test();
        }
    }